task.title: [Enhancement] Integrate "Settings" Tab Feature for Gauzy AI Configuration
task.description:
For the "Settings" tab, we are introducing two critical settings to enhance user control and privacy within the Gauzy AI platform. These settings will govern the behavior of job search and matching analyses, as well as employee performance analysis. The goal is to provide users with the ability to customize their experience and manage the data shared with Gauzy AI.

**Settings:**

1. **Enable Jobs Search & Matching Analysis**

> - Type: Switch (true/false)
> - Description: This setting controls the activation of job search and matching analyses performed by Gauzy AI. When enabled, users will benefit from enhanced job search capabilities and improved matching accuracy. If disabled, the "Browse" and "Matching" menu items in the Jobs menu should be hidden to ensure a streamlined user interface.

2. **Enable Employee Performance Analysis**

> - Type: Switch (true/false)
> - Description: This setting governs the transmission of employee work metrics, including keyboard inputs, mouse movements, and screenshots, to Gauzy AI for analysis. Enabling this option allows for comprehensive performance analysis. However, if disabled, Gauzy AI will not receive and analyze screenshots or any other detailed input, ensuring strict user privacy and control over data sharing.


**Note:** Integrate these settings into the "Settings" tab on the Gauzy AI integration page: [Gauzy AI Integration Page](https://app.gauzy.co/#/pages/integrations/gauzy-ai/{{UUID}}).
